The energy sector is broadly divided between demand for energy and supply of energy to the economy. The draft SNEP document was therefore divided into two volumes to facilitate ease of discussion:
* Volume One covered the Demand Sectors of the Economy, namely Residential
* Volume Two covered the supply-side of the energy sector, namely, electricity;

Defining the contextual framework within which the SNEP operates is imperative. There are local and international factors that could significantly influence policy decisions. The SNEP energy policy framework has thus been formulated within the following settings:
* The existing socio-economic and environmental policies;
